3. WCAG CONTRAST ANALYSIS — MATHEMATICAL PROOF
========================================================================

We calculated exact WCAG 2.2 contrast ratios using the official relative
luminance formula for every color pair in UNJYNX light mode:

3.1 TEXT COLORS ON #F8F5FF BACKGROUND

Color                          Hex       Ratio    AA Normal  AA Large  AAA
Midnight Purple (primary text) #1A0533   17.51:1  PASS       PASS      PASS
Brand Violet (links/accents)   #6B21A8    8.10:1  PASS       PASS      PASS
Slate 600 (tertiary text)      #475569    7.04:1  PASS       PASS      PASS
Rich Gold (CTA buttons, large) #B8860B    3.02:1  FAIL       PASS      FAIL
Deep Emerald (success)         #059669    3.50:1  FAIL       PASS      FAIL
Deep Rose (error/overdue)      #E11D48    4.36:1  FAIL       PASS      FAIL

3.2 CRITICAL INSIGHTS

a) #1A0533 vs #000000 as text color:
   - #1A0533 on #F8F5FF = 17.51:1 (AAA)
   - #000000 on #FFFFFF = 21.00:1 (AAA)
   Both exceed AAA. But #1A0533 is BRANDED -- it carries the purple identity
   into every line of text. Black is generic. Purple is UNJYNX.

b) WHY #FFD700 FAILS on light:
   - #FFD700 on #F8F5FF = 1.30:1 -- CATASTROPHIC FAILURE
   - #FFD700 on #FFFFFF = 1.40:1 -- equally terrible
   Electric gold literally disappears on light backgrounds. This is why
   we MUST use #B8860B (Rich Gold / Dark Goldenrod) in light mode.
   #B8860B provides 3.02:1 which passes AA for large text (>=18pt or 14pt bold).

c) Notion comparison:
   - Notion: #37352F on #FFFFFF = 12.26:1
   - UNJYNX: #1A0533 on #F8F5FF = 17.51:1
   UNJYNX has 43% BETTER contrast than Notion. Our text is more readable
   AND more branded. This is a measurable competitive advantage.

d) Semantic colors all pass AA Large (>=3:1):
   - Rich Gold: 3.02:1 (buttons, badges, headings at >=18pt)
   - Deep Emerald: 3.50:1 (success states, connected indicators)
   - Deep Rose: 4.36:1 (error states, overdue indicators)

   For normal text size, these semantic colors should be used WITH a
   midnight purple label adjacent. Example: a rose-colored overdue badge
   should have #1A0533 text, not #E11D48 text at small sizes.

e) Surface variations maintain contrast:
   - #1A0533 on #F0EAFC (Light Lavender) = 16.06:1 (AAA)
   - #1A0533 on #EDE5F7 (Card Surface) = 15.40:1 (AAA)
   Even on tinted surfaces, primary text exceeds AAA.

