5. 2026 LIGHT MODE DESIGN TRENDS
========================================================================

Based on research across Envato Elements, Updivision, DesignRush, Chop Dawg,
Designity, and NativelyDev trend reports for 2025-2026:

5.1 ELEVATED NEUTRALS (Primary Trend)

In 2026, bright white will feel too sterile and processed. Creamy,
imperfect colors are more likely to make their mark -- imagining textures
of oat milk, undyed wool, and limestone.

UNJYNX application: #F8F5FF is our elevated neutral -- it is not cream
or beige (which would clash with purple). It is PURPLE cream. The elevated
neutral that matches our brand.

5.2 HYPER-SATURATED ACCENTS ON NEUTRAL BASES

Bold, vibrant pops of color against minimal layouts that guide attention
and reduce cognitive load. Purple + gold on a neutral purple-mist base
is the PERFECT execution of this trend.

5.3 SOFT GRADIENTS 2.0

Subtle, airy blends that feel more like light passing through glass --
pastel transitions, gentle color shifts. This describes our living
gradient background: #F8F5FF to #F0EAFC with faint lavender shimmer.

5.4 ADAPTIVE COLOR SYSTEMS

Palettes that respond to lighting conditions. Our productivity-state-
driven background (idle, productive, all-done, overdue) is an advanced
implementation of this trend.

5.5 MISTY LAVENDER / SOFT-TECH PASTELS

Misty lavenders, washed pinks, gentle mauves, and cool bluish purples
that blend dreamy calm with a subtle digital edge. This LITERALLY
describes our light mode palette.

UNJYNX is not following these trends -- we are at their intersection.
Our light mode sits exactly where 2026 design is heading.

========================================================================
6. APPLE LIQUID GLASS & LIGHT MODE
========================================================================

6.1 WHAT IS LIQUID GLASS?

Announced June 9, 2025 at WWDC, Liquid Glass is Apple unified visual
language across iOS 26, iPadOS 26, macOS Tahoe, watchOS 26, and tvOS 26.

Key properties:
- Real-time light bending (lensing)
- Specular highlights responding to device motion
- Adaptive shadows
- Translucent material that refracts surroundings
- Transitions between light/dark modes seamlessly
- New transparent clear mode

6.2 FLUTTER IMPLEMENTATION: liquid_glass_widgets

Package: liquid_glass_widgets (v0.4.0-dev.4)
License: MIT
Platforms: iOS, Android, macOS, Web, Windows, Linux
Total widgets: 32

Widget categories:
- Containers: GlassContainer, GlassCard, GlassPanel
- Interactive: GlassButton, GlassIconButton, GlassChip, GlassSwitch, GlassSlider
- Input: GlassTextField, GlassSearchBar, GlassPicker
- Feedback: GlassProgressIndicator, GlassToast, GlassSnackBar
- Overlays: GlassDialog, GlassSheet, GlassActionSheet, GlassMenu
- Surfaces: GlassAppBar, GlassBottomBar, GlassTabBar, GlassSideBar

Customization via LiquidGlassSettings:
- thickness (0.0-1.0): Material depth
- blur: Frosted effect intensity
- refractiveIndex (1.0-2.0): Light bending
- glassColor: Tint with opacity
- lightAngle: Directional lighting (degrees)
- lightIntensity: Lighting strength
- ambientStrength: Ambient contribution
- saturation: Color intensity multiplier
- chromaticAberration: Color separation effect

Quality modes:
- Standard: Lightweight fragment shader (all platforms)
- Premium: Advanced texture capture + chromatic aberration (Impeller only)

6.3 UNJYNX LIGHT MODE WITH LIQUID GLASS

For UNJYNX light mode, we configure Liquid Glass with purple tinting:

  LiquidGlassSettings(
    thickness: 0.6,
    blur: 8.0,
    refractiveIndex: 1.2,
    glassColor: Color(0xA6FFFFFF),  // white 65% opacity
    lightAngle: 315.0,              // top-left light source
    lightIntensity: 0.4,            // subtle, not overwhelming
    ambientStrength: 0.3,
    saturation: 1.1,                // slightly boost purple tint
    chromaticAberration: 0.02,      // very subtle color split
  )

For dark mode, increase blur to 12, reduce glassColor opacity to 8%,
and increase lightIntensity to 0.6 for the frosted glow effect.

6.4 LIQUID GLASS vs TRADITIONAL GLASSMORPHISM

Apple Liquid Glass improves on traditional glassmorphism:
- Traditional: Static blur + border + shadow
- Liquid Glass: Dynamic refraction + motion-responsive highlights + depth

For UNJYNX, we use BOTH:
- Liquid Glass widgets for navigation bars, tab bars, sheets (system chrome)
- Traditional glassmorphism for content cards (more control over brand tinting)

This hybrid approach gives us Apple premium feel while maintaining
our purple-tinted brand identity on content surfaces.

========================================================================
7. LIGHT GLASSMORPHISM — TECHNIQUE DEEP-DIVE
========================================================================

7.1 WHY LIGHT GLASSMORPHISM IS DIFFERENT

Dark glassmorphism: translucent white on dark = FROSTED GLASS GLOW
Light glassmorphism: translucent white on light = SOFT FROSTED PANE

On dark backgrounds:
- Low opacity (5-15%) creates visible glass because of HIGH contrast
- Blur diffuses the dark background creating ethereal glow
- Borders can be very subtle (white 10% opacity)
- Shadows are optional (the glow IS the depth)

On light backgrounds:
- Low opacity is INVISIBLE -- you need 50-80% for glass to be visible
- Blur must be LESS (6-10px vs 10-20px) -- light bgs do not need diffusion
- Borders MUST be visible -- without them, cards melt into background
- Shadows are REQUIRED -- they create the depth that glow creates in dark

7.2 UNJYNX LIGHT GLASS CARD SPECIFICATION

  ClipRRect(
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16),
    child: BackdropFilter(
      filter: ImageFilter.blur(sigmaX: 8, sigmaY: 8),
      child: Container(
        decoration: BoxDecoration(
          color: Colors.white.withOpacity(0.65),
          borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16),
          border: Border.all(
            color: Color(0x146B21A8),  // Brand Violet at 8% opacity
            width: 1.0,
          ),
          boxShadow: [
            BoxShadow(
              color: Color(0x0F1A0533),  // Midnight Purple at 6% opacity
              blurRadius: 8,
              offset: Offset(0, 2),
            ),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    ),
  )

7.3 DARK VS LIGHT GLASS COMPARISON TABLE

Property          Dark Mode              Light Mode
Blur sigma        12px                   8px
Glass opacity     8% white               65% white
Border color      white 10%              violet 8%
Border width      0.5px                  1.0px
Shadow            optional               REQUIRED
Shadow color      n/a                    rgba(26,5,51,0.06)
Shadow blur       n/a                    8px
Shadow offset     n/a                    (0, 2)
Background needed Deep dark (#0F0A1A)    Purple mist (#F8F5FF)
Card feel         Frosted glow           Frosted lavender pane
Depth mechanism   Glow/luminance         Shadow/elevation

7.4 HERO CARD GLASS (Higher Emphasis)

For hero cards (daily content card, streak card, AI Whisper):
  - Blur: 12px (more than standard)
  - Opacity: 75% white
  - Border: gradient from violet to rich gold (1.5px)
  - Shadow: 12px blur, (0, 4) offset, rgba(26,5,51,0.10)
  - Optional: very subtle gradient tint in glass
    (white 75% to FFF8E1 gold wash 10%)

7.5 INTERACTIVE GLASS STATES

Rest:    65% white, 8px blur, violet border 8%, shadow 6%
Hover:   70% white, 8px blur, violet border 12%, shadow 8%
Pressed: 60% white, 6px blur, violet border 15%, shadow 4%, scale(0.98)
Focused: 65% white, 8px blur, violet border 25% (2px), shadow 6%
Active:  Gold wash fill (#FFF8E1 20%), 8px blur, gold border 15%, shadow 8%

7.6 PERFORMANCE CONSIDERATIONS

BackdropFilter is expensive. Mitigations:
- Use RepaintBoundary around glass containers
- Limit blur sigma to <=12px on mobile
- Avoid nesting glass effects (glass inside glass)
- Use Impeller renderer (default in Flutter 3.27+) for hardware blur
- Consider saveLayer for complex glass compositions
- Profile: target <=2ms per glass card on mid-range devices

========================================================================
8. MATERIAL DESIGN 3 LIGHT THEME IMPLEMENTATION
========================================================================

8.1 ColorScheme.fromSeed WITH PURPLE

Flutter Material 3 generates a complete color scheme from a seed color:

  final lightColorScheme = ColorScheme.fromSeed(
    seedColor: Color(0xFF6B21A8),  // Brand Violet
    brightness: Brightness.light,
  );

This generates harmonious tonal palettes. However, for UNJYNX we override
specific values to match our exact brand:

  final unjynxLightColorScheme = ColorScheme.fromSeed(
    seedColor: Color(0xFF6B21A8),
    brightness: Brightness.light,
    // Custom overrides
    primary: Color(0xFF6B21A8),         // Brand Violet
    onPrimary: Colors.white,
    primaryContainer: Color(0xFFEDE5F7), // Card Surface
    onPrimaryContainer: Color(0xFF1A0533),
    secondary: Color(0xFFB8860B),        // Rich Gold
    onSecondary: Colors.white,
    secondaryContainer: Color(0xFFFFF8E1), // Gold Wash
    onSecondaryContainer: Color(0xFF5C4300),
    tertiary: Color(0xFF059669),          // Deep Emerald
    onTertiary: Colors.white,
    surface: Color(0xFFF8F5FF),           // Purple Mist background
    onSurface: Color(0xFF1A0533),         // Midnight Purple text
    surfaceContainerLowest: Color(0xFFFFFFFF),
    surfaceContainerLow: Color(0xFFF8F5FF),
    surfaceContainer: Color(0xFFF0EAFC),
    surfaceContainerHigh: Color(0xFFEDE5F7),
    surfaceContainerHighest: Color(0xFFE5DCEF),
    error: Color(0xFFE11D48),             // Deep Rose
    onError: Colors.white,
    outline: Color(0x146B21A8),           // Violet 8% for borders
    outlineVariant: Color(0x0A6B21A8),    // Violet 4% for dividers
    shadow: Color(0xFF1A0533),            // Purple shadow base
  );

8.2 ThemeData CONFIGURATION

  ThemeData unjynxLightTheme = ThemeData(
    useMaterial3: true,
    colorScheme: unjynxLightColorScheme,
    scaffoldBackgroundColor: Color(0xFFF8F5FF),
    appBarTheme: AppBarTheme(
      backgroundColor: Colors.transparent,
      elevation: 0,
      scrolledUnderElevation: 0,
      titleTextStyle: TextStyle(
        fontFamily: 'Outfit',
        fontSize: 20,
        fontWeight: FontWeight.w600,
        color: Color(0xFF1A0533),
      ),
    ),
    cardTheme: CardThemeData(
      color: Colors.white.withOpacity(0.65),
      elevation: 0,
      shape: RoundedRectangleBorder(
        borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16),
        side: BorderSide(
          color: Color(0x146B21A8),
          width: 1,
        ),
      ),
    ),
  );

8.3 SURFACE TINT VS SHADOW ELEVATION

Material 3 uses tonal elevation (surface tint) in light mode by default.
For UNJYNX, we OVERRIDE this with shadow elevation because:

- Tonal elevation uses a primary color tint overlay that conflicts with
  our purple mist background (it is purple ON purple -- no differentiation)
- Shadow elevation with purple-tinted shadows creates clear card boundaries
- Our glass cards already have BackdropFilter for depth -- tonal overlay
  would interfere with the glass effect

Override: surfaceTintColor: Colors.transparent to disable M3 tonal elevation.
Use custom BoxShadow with purple tint instead.

