========================================================================
23. THE UNJYNX LIGHT MODE DIFFERENTIATOR
========================================================================

23.1 WHAT MAKES UNJYNX LIGHT MODE UNIQUE

No productivity app combines ALL of these in light mode:

1. PURPLE MIST BACKGROUND (#F8F5FF) -- warm, branded, not white
2. MIDNIGHT PURPLE TEXT (#1A0533) -- branded text, not generic black
3. RICH GOLD ACCENTS (#B8860B) -- premium, not blue/red/gray
4. PURPLE-TINTED SHADOWS -- warm depth, not cold gray elevation
5. DUAL GLASSMORPHISM -- Liquid Glass (system) + traditional (content)
6. LIVING GRADIENT -- productivity-state-driven subtle background shifts
7. GOLD WASH SELECTIONS (#FFF8E1) -- warm active states, not blue highlight
8. RIVE ANIMATIONS -- interactive, state-driven, light-adapted
9. DEEPER SEMANTIC COLORS -- properly contrast-checked for light
10. GHOST MODE DRAMATIC ENTRY -- light to dark transition as a design moment

23.2 THE BRAND PROMISE

A user who uses light mode should feel like UNJYNX was DESIGNED for light mode.
A user who uses dark mode should feel like UNJYNX was DESIGNED for dark mode.
Neither should feel like the afterthought. That is the standard.

23.3 MEASURABLE ADVANTAGES

vs Todoist:  43% better text contrast ratio (17.51:1 vs 12.26:1)
vs Notion:   Branded bg vs generic white. Purple identity vs neutral.
vs TickTick: Unique color scheme vs generic blue. Gold vs gray.
vs Things 3: Personality vs asceticism. Gamification vs none.
vs Linear:   Pervasive purple vs accent-only violet.

